  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of the study is to evaluate the feasibility of a rapid HIV testing program in the
      Temple University Hospital(TUH)Emergency Department. We hypothesize that a rapid HIV testing
      program in the TUH Emergency Department is feasible. Patients presenting to the Adult TUH
      Emergency Department with certain conditions will be offered rapid HIV testing. Testing will
      be performed by oral swab using the OraQuick Advance test. Patients will receive post-test
      counseling.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
